### 분류 모델의 평가 항목 ###

**Confusion Matrx**

![image-20231203200952404](/images/2023-12-03-Model Evaluation/image-20231203200952404.png)

1종 오류 -> 가설이 아닌데 맞다고 할 확률 

2종 오류 -> 가설이 맞는데 기각할 확률 



#### Accuracy ####

$accuracy = \frac{TP + TN}{TP + TN + FP + FN}$

#### Precision ####

$precision = \frac{TP}{TP + FP}$

#### Recall ####

$recall = \frac{TP}{TP + FN}$

#### Fall-out (FPR) ####

$accuracy = \frac{FP}{FP + TN}$

* We can start to think about when recall would be important as compared to when precision would be important
* For instance if it is a problem of screening cancer patients a False Positive may be a lot less harmful compared to a False Negative 
* In such a case we would prefer to achieve higher recall by lowering the threshold 



#### F1-Score ####

$F_1 =\frac{2 * precision * recall}{precision + recall}$



### ROC와 AUC 

![image-20231203202542587](/images/2023-12-03-Model Evaluation/image-20231203202542587.png)

![image-20231203202559128](/images/2023-12-03-Model Evaluation/image-20231203202559128.png)

* TPR -> Recall, FPR -> Fall-out
* Plot by adjusting the threshold




#### ROC 커브 그려보기 

```python
import numpy as np 
import pandas as pd 
```


```python
red_url = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PinkWink/ML_tutorial/master/dataset/winequality-red.csv"
white_url = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PinkWink/ML_tutorial/master/dataset/winequality-white.csv"

red_wine = pd.read_csv(red_url, sep=";")
white_wine = pd.read_csv(white_url, sep=";")
```


```python
red_wine['color'] = 1 
white_wine['color'] = 0 

wine = pd.concat([red_wine, white_wine], axis=0)
X = wine.drop(['color'], axis = 1)
y = wine['color']
```


```python
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier 
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score 

X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.2,
                                                    random_state = 13)

wine_tree = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=2, random_state=13)
wine_tree.fit(X_train, y_train)

y_pred_tr = wine_tree.predict(X_train)
y_pred_test = wine_tree.predict(X_test)
```


```python
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, precision_score 
from sklearn.metrics import recall_score, f1_score
from sklearn.metrics import roc_auc_score, roc_curve 

print(f'Train Accuracy : ', accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_test))
print(f'Recall : {recall_score(y_test, y_pred_test)}')
print(f'Precision : {precision_score(y_test, y_pred_test)}')
print(f'AUC Score : {roc_auc_score(y_test, y_pred_test)}')
print(f'F1 Score : {f1_score(y_test, y_pred_test)}')
```

#### 로그함수 그려보기



```python
def log(x, base): 
    return np.log(x)/np.log(base)  # 성질임 기초수학 한 번 다시 보자 ㅠㅠ

x1 = np.linspace(0.0001, 5, 1000)
x2 = np.linspace(0.01, 5, 100)

y11, y12 = log(x1, 10), log(x2, np.e)
y21, y22 = log(x1, 1/10), log(x2, 1/np.e)
```


```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt 

fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12,6))

ax[0].plot(x1, y11, label='$\log_{10} x$', color='k')
ax[0].plot(x2, y12,'--', label='$\log_{e} x$', color ='k')
ax[0].set_xlabel('$x$', fontsize=25)
ax[0].set_ylabel('$y$', fontsize=25)
ax[0].legend(fontsize=20, loc='lower right')

ax[1].plot(x1, y21, label='$\log_{1/10} x$', color='k')
ax[1].plot(x2, y22,'--', label='$\log_{1/e} x$', color ='k')
ax[1].set_xlabel('$x$', fontsize=25)
ax[1].set_ylabel('$y$', fontsize=25)
ax[1].legend(fontsize=20, loc='upper right')
```

```python
q1 = np.percentile(samples, 25)
q2 = np.percentile(samples, 50)
q3 = np.percentile(samples, 75)
upper_fence = q3 + iqr * 1.5 
lower_fence = q1 - iqr * 1.5 
```


```python
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 4))
plt.scatter(samples, tmp_y)

plt.axvline(x=q1, color='black')
plt.axvline(x=q2, color='red')
plt.axvline(x=q3, color='black')
plt.axvline(x=upper_fence, color='black', ls='dashed')
```
